# IntelliJ IDEA tricks
- source: https://www.udemy.com/intellij-idea-secrets-double-your-coding-speed-in-2-hours/
- keymap: see Preferences - Keymap: Keymaps (top left): Default For XWin

## Navigate between texts
- the usual ctrl+left/right / home / end
- page up/down to scroll page
- ctrl + home/end to move to beginning / end of current file (works)

## Camel Humps
- TimeLimitedEntry through TLE (known)

## Moving Lines and Statements, Duplicate & Delete lines
- move line: shift + alt + up/down
- move statement: shift + ctrl + up/down
	- does not need preselection for loops / if / ... (good to know, previously sometimes confusing)
- duplicate: ctrl + d
- delete line: ctrl + y

## Parameter information
- show parameter information of method: ctrl + p

## comment code
- (un)comment single line: ctrl + /
- block (un)comment: shift + ctrl + /

## fold and expand code
- fold method: ctrl + "-"
- expand method: ctrl + "+"

## navigate to X, search everywhere
- navigate to class: ctrl + n, supports partial match, camel humps, wildcard search
- navigate back: ctrl + alt + left (really useful)
- navigate to symbol: shift + ctrl + alt + n => search for operations, filterable by class-prefix (really useful)
- navigate to file: shift + ctrl + n 
	- folders also possible, ending with '/', by path: dir/filename
- navigate to action: shift + ctrl + a (f.e. current 'theme', current 'java compiler', 'increase' fontsize)
- search everywhere: double shift, tab through sections

## tab management
- disable: shift + ctrl + a 'tab place' none
- navigate to recent files: ctrl + e, search through typing
- recent edited files: shift + ctrl + e

## text selection
- select by word: shift + ctrl + left/right
- select cursor to end of line: shift + home / end
- extend/shrink selection: ctrl + [shift] + w

## smart completion
- invoke smart code completion after 'new ': shift + ctrl + space
- also for list of parameters in method call (constants), return statements
- static method for factory-usage / collections / ... by shift + ctrl + space twice
	- assertSame autocomp twice => Assert.assertSame()
- add static import: alt + enter (without prefix)
- postfix completion: s.notnull | null | synch | try | for | fori | forr => !=null check... reversed for
- configure postfix completion: ctrl + shift + a 'postfix comple' (great!)

## generate code
- getter/setter/constructor/equals/hashcode: alt + insert
- testMethods/setUp/tearDown: alt + insert

## version control (git/svn)
- commit changes: ctrl + k
	- compare file in commit changes dialog: ctrl + d 
	- revert file in commit changes dialog: alt + ctrl + z
- VSC Operations: alt + back quote
	- checkout branch number 7, type name
	- annotate 5, shows log (annotation panel), select, diff via enter (brilliant!)

## reformatting code
- nothing selected, format file: ctrl + alt + l
	- select method via ctrl + w and reformat method only
- move focus to project tool window: alt + 1 and format all in package

## optimize import
- remove unused and order imports: ctrl + alt + o
- optimize imports on the fly: shift + ctrl + a 'optimize imports on the fly'
- also possible for commits (right panel)

## navigating to compilation error
- start compilation: ctrl + f9 (searched that some time!)
	- first error in focus via escape, then fix
	- navigate to next compilation error: ctrl + alt + up/down

## language injection
- string, alt + enter => inject language/reference (nice for regex/...)
	- alt + enter => edit json fragment (in new editor), auto-escaped
	- close other editor: ctrl + f4
